com.google.api.client.googleapis.media
Class MediaHttpDownloader

java.lang.Object
  com.google.api.client.googleapis.media.MediaHttpDownloader

public final class MediaHttpDownloader
extends java.lang.Object

Media HTTP Downloader, with support for both direct and resumable media downloads. Documentation is available here.

Implementation is not thread-safe.

Since:
1.9
Author:
rmistry@google.com (Ravi Mistry)

Field Detail

MAXIMUM_CHUNK_SIZE

public static final int MAXIMUM_CHUNK_SIZE
Default maximum number of bytes that will be downloaded from the server in any single HTTP request. Set to 32MB because that is the maximum App Engine request size.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

requestFactory

private final HttpRequestFactory requestFactory
The request factory for connections to the server.

transport

private final HttpTransport transport
The transport to use for requests.

backOffPolicyEnabled

private boolean backOffPolicyEnabled
Determines whether the back off policy is enabled or disabled. If value is set to false then server errors are not handled and the download process will fail if a server error is encountered. Defaults to true.

directDownloadEnabled

private boolean directDownloadEnabled
Determines whether direct media download is enabled or disabled. If value is set to true then a direct download will be done where the whole media content is downloaded in a single request. If value is set to false then the download uses the resumable media download protocol to download in data chunks. Defaults to false.

progressListener

private MediaHttpDownloaderProgressListener progressListener
Progress listener to send progress notifications to or null for none.

chunkSize

private int chunkSize
Maximum size of individual chunks that will get downloaded by single HTTP requests. The default value is MAXIMUM_CHUNK_SIZE.

mediaContentLength

private long mediaContentLength
The length of the HTTP media content or 0 before it is initialized in setMediaContentLength(java.lang.String).

downloadState

private MediaHttpDownloader.DownloadState downloadState
The current state of the downloader.

bytesDownloaded

private long bytesDownloaded
The total number of bytes downloaded by this downloader.

Method Detail

download

public void download(GenericUrl requestUrl,
                     java.io.OutputStream outputStream)
              throws java.io.IOException
Executes a direct media download or a resumable media download.

This method does not close the given output stream.

This method is not reentrant. A new instance of MediaHttpDownloader must be instantiated before download called be called again.

Parameters:
requestUrl - The request URL where the download requests will be sent
outputStream - destination output stream
Throws:
java.io.IOException

getNextByteIndex

private long getNextByteIndex(java.lang.String rangeHeader)
Returns the next byte index identifying data that the server has not yet sent out, obtained from the HTTP Content-Range header (E.g a header of "Content-Range: 0-55/1000" would cause 56 to be returned). null headers cause 0 to be returned.

Parameters:
rangeHeader - in the HTTP response
Returns:
the byte index beginning where the server has yet to send out data

setBytesDownloaded

public MediaHttpDownloader setBytesDownloaded(long bytesDownloaded)
Sets the total number of bytes that have been downloaded of the media resource.

If a download was aborted mid-way due to a connection failure then users can resume the download from the point where it left off.

This method is only applicable for resumable media download.

Parameters:
bytesDownloaded - The total number of bytes downloaded

setMediaContentLength

private void setMediaContentLength(java.lang.String rangeHeader)
Sets the media content length from the HTTP Content-Range header (E.g a header of "Content-Range: 0-55/1000" would cause 1000 to be set. null headers do not set anything.

Parameters:
rangeHeader - in the HTTP response

isDirectDownloadEnabled

public boolean isDirectDownloadEnabled()
Returns whether direct media download is enabled or disabled. If value is set to true then a direct download will be done where the whole media content is downloaded in a single request. If value is set to false then the download uses the resumable media download protocol to download in data chunks. Defaults to false.
